420
00:40:53,618 --> 00:40:56,580
Samper is not going anywhere.

421
00:40:56,705 --> 00:41:00,208
Well, at least people know the truth.

422
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:10,343
I want you gone, Peña.
So do the Colombians.

423
00:41:10,469 --> 00:41:12,304
I understand, sir.

424
00:41:19,686 --> 00:41:24,524
You know, any aspirations you had
for your career...

425
00:41:26,193 --> 00:41:29,112
...just got dragged
behind the barn and shot.

426
00:41:33,450 --> 00:41:36,411
I resigned from the DEA this morning.

427
00:41:48,965 --> 00:41:53,303
'Recordings that link the president
with narcotrafficking have been leaked.'

428
00:41:53,428 --> 00:41:55,430
'The reality is that
they need five million.

429
00:41:55,555 --> 00:41:57,974
- 'Uh-huh.'
- 'We're missing three, see?'

430
00:41:58,099 --> 00:41:59,809
- 'We have it.'
- 'Yes?'

431
00:41:59,935 --> 00:42:01,394
'Yes, that's done.'

432
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:04,523
'This scandal threatens elected president
Ernesto Samper's career

433
00:42:04,648 --> 00:42:08,360
'if the authorities confirm his campaign
was funded by narcotrafficking money.'

434
00:42:08,485 --> 00:42:12,322
'President Samper,
the only solution is your resignation!'

435
00:42:12,447 --> 00:42:16,409
'Colombians can be certain...

436
00:42:19,829 --> 00:42:25,835
'...that if they prove
any money transfer of any kind,

437
00:42:25,961 --> 00:42:30,757
'the deposit would've been made
behind my back.'

438
00:42:31,925 --> 00:42:36,346
'The Colombians called
the scandal "Proceso 8000".

439
00:42:37,681 --> 00:42:40,517
'And it set into motion
a series of events

440
00:42:40,642 --> 00:42:44,437
'that finally brought the reign
of the Cali godfathers to an end.

441
00:42:46,356 --> 00:42:50,318
'Chepe Santacruz never did make it
back to New York.

442
00:42:51,903 --> 00:42:55,865
'Without the government's guarantee
that their sentences would be minimal,

443
00:42:55,991 --> 00:43:00,370
'Chepe decided that prison wasn't
the best place for him to be.

444
00:43:01,079 --> 00:43:03,957
'And so, he released himself...

445
00:43:05,542 --> 00:43:08,253
'...and set out in search of new alliances,

446
00:43:08,378 --> 00:43:11,089
'with partners who could help him
rebuild the empire.

447
00:43:11,214 --> 00:43:13,300
'You won't believe who he chose.'

448
00:43:15,635 --> 00:43:16,886
Don Chepe.

449
00:43:18,847 --> 00:43:20,765
I was happy to get your call.

450
00:43:22,434 --> 00:43:25,645
'Predictably,
it wasn't much of a partnership.

451
00:43:25,770 --> 00:43:29,357
'It seems the Castaños expected
a larger contribution to their cause...

452
00:43:31,401 --> 00:43:34,279
'...than Chepe was comfortable making.

453
00:43:35,363 --> 00:43:38,158
'So the alliance died quickly.

454
00:43:38,283 --> 00:43:42,078
'And Chepe Santacruz's wild ride
came to an end.

455
00:43:44,497 --> 00:43:47,751
'Pacho Herrera didn't fare
much better staying in jail.

456
00:43:47,876 --> 00:43:50,086
'Vendettas in the drug game
never end.'

457
00:43:51,588 --> 00:43:54,257
'And Pacho's war on the Salazars

458
00:43:54,382 --> 00:43:57,052
'made him some lifelong
North Valley enemies.

459
00:44:01,848 --> 00:44:03,308
Motherfucker!

460
00:44:06,895 --> 00:44:09,189
'And as for
the Rodríguez-Orejuela brothers,

461
00:44:09,314 --> 00:44:13,193
'political pressure from the U.S.
and a disgraced Colombian president

462
00:44:13,318 --> 00:44:16,363
'who needed to prove
he was tough on narcos

463
00:44:16,488 --> 00:44:22,535
'brought back the only effective weapon
